The paper deals with image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the important components of the framework and the factors that impact the efficiency of training a deep CNN, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of CNNs for image classification also involves optimization techniques, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of the proposed framework with existing models, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
